721384f.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 56th Street
721384f.text:
Madison Avenue, east side, from 57th to 5oth Streets, the old
Iester Studio building remodelled by Joseph D. Leland
Company for the Anderson Gallenies. The Fifth Avenue Association
awarded its silver medal for this alteration.
About 1923.
Cift of E. M. Jenks.

721393f-a.title: Manhattan: Madison Avenue - 56th Street
721393f-a.text:
Construction of Fuller Building, Madison Avenue at N.E. corner
of 57th Street.
At the right, on the east side from 5uth to 57th Streets, may be
seen the Anderson Art Galleries.
The view is from 5dth Street, looking north on the east side.
March 8, 1929.
Photograph by George A. Fuller Co.
ift of Walker & Gillette.
